#: ../../manual/animation/armatures/posing/bone_constraints/inverse_kinematics/spline_ik.rst:5
msgid "Spline IK"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/animation/armatures/posing/bone_constraints/inverse_kinematics/spline_ik.rst:7
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Spline IK is a constraint which aligns a chain of bones along a curve. By"
" leveraging the ease and flexibility of achieving aesthetically pleasing "
"shapes offered by curves and the predictability and well integrated "
"control offered by bones, Spline IK is an invaluable tool in the riggers'"
" toolbox. It is particularly well suited for rigging flexible body parts "
"such as tails, tentacles, and spines, as well as inorganic items such as "
"ropes."
msgstr ""
"*Spline IK* est une contrainte qui aligne une chaîne d'os le long d'une "
"courbe. En exploitant la facilité et la flexibilité d'obtenir "
"esthétiquement des formes plaisantes offertes par les courbes et la "
"prédictibilité et le contrôle bien intégré offerts par les os, *Spline "
"IK* est un outil inestimable dans la boîte à outils des riggeurs. Il est "
"particulièrement bien adapté pour faire le rig des parties de corps "
"flexible telles que des queues, des tentacules, et des rachis, ainsi que "
"des éléments inorganiques tels que des cordes."

#: ../../manual/animation/armatures/posing/bone_constraints/inverse_kinematics/spline_ik.rst:14
msgid ""
"Full description of the settings for the spline IK can be found on the "
":doc:`Spline IK </animation/constraints/tracking/spline_ik>` page."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/animation/armatures/posing/bone_constraints/inverse_kinematics/spline_ik.rst:19
msgid "Basic Setup"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/animation/armatures/posing/bone_constraints/inverse_kinematics/spline_ik.rst:21
msgid ""
"The Spline IK Constraint is not strictly an 'Inverse Kinematics' method "
"(i.e. IK Constraint), but rather a 'Forward Kinematics' method (i.e. "
"normal bone posing). However, it still shares some characteristics of the"
" IK Constraint, such as operating on multiple bones not being usable for "
"Objects, and being evaluated after all other constraints have been "
"evaluated. It should be noted that if a Standard IK chain and a Spline IK"
" chain both affect a bone at the same time the Standard IK chain takes "
"priority. Such setups are best avoided though, since the results may be "
"difficult to control."
msgstr ""
"La contrainte *Spline IK* n'est pas formellement une méthode \"Inverse "
"Kinematics\" (à savoir Contrainte IK), mais plutôt une méthode \"Forward "
"Kinematics\" (càd. pose d'os normale). Cependant, il partage toujours "
"certaines caractéristiques de la Contrainte IK, telles que sur plusieurs "
"os non utilisables pour des Objets, et évalués après toutes les autres "
"contraintes. Il devrait être noté que si une chaîne IK standard et une "
"chaîne Apline IK affectent toutes les deux  un os en même temps la chaîne"
" IK standard a la priorité. De telles configurations sont toutefois à "
"éviter car les résultats peuvent être difficiles à contrôler."

#: ../../manual/animation/armatures/posing/bone_constraints/inverse_kinematics/spline_ik.rst:30
msgid ""
"To setup Spline IK, it is necessary to have a chain of connected bones "
"and a curve to constrain these bones to:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/animation/armatures/posing/bone_constraints/inverse_kinematics/spline_ik.rst:33
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"With the last bone in the chain selected, add a :doc:`Spline IK "
"</animation/constraints/tracking/spline_ik>` Constraint from the Bone "
"Constraints tab in the Properties Editor."
msgstr ""
"Avec le dernier os dans la chaîne sélectionné, ajoutez une Contrainte "
":doc:`Spline IK </rigging/constraints/tracking/spline_ik>`de l'onglet "
"*Bone Constraints* dans l'Éditeur properties."

#: ../../manual/animation/armatures/posing/bone_constraints/inverse_kinematics/spline_ik.rst:36
msgid ""
"Set the 'Chain Length' setting to the number of bones in the chain "
"(starting from and including the selected bone) that should be influenced"
" by the curve."
msgstr ""
"Définissez le paramètre *Chain Length* au nombre d'os dans la chaîne (en "
"commençant par et comprenant l'os sélectionné) qui devrait être influencé"
" par la courbe."

#: ../../manual/animation/armatures/posing/bone_constraints/inverse_kinematics/spline_ik.rst:38
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Finally, set the 'Target' field to the curve that should control the "
"curve."
msgstr ""
"Enfin, définissez le champ \"Target\" à la courbe qui devrait contrôler "
"la courbe."

#: ../../manual/animation/armatures/posing/bone_constraints/inverse_kinematics/spline_ik.rst:40
msgid "Congratulations, the bone chain is now controlled by the curve."
msgstr "Félicitations, la chaîne d'os est maintenant contrôlée par la courbe."

#: ../../manual/animation/armatures/posing/bone_constraints/inverse_kinematics/spline_ik.rst:44
msgid "Settings and Controls"
msgstr "Paramètres et contrôles"

#: ../../manual/animation/armatures/posing/bone_constraints/inverse_kinematics/spline_ik.rst:47
msgid "Roll Control"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/animation/armatures/posing/bone_constraints/inverse_kinematics/spline_ik.rst:49
msgid ""
"To control the 'twist' or 'roll' of the Spline IK chain, the standard "
"methods of rotating the bones in the chain along their Y axes still "
"apply. For example, simply rotate the bones in the chain around their Y "
"axes to adjust the roll of the chain from that point onwards. Applying "
"copy rotation constraints on the bones should also work."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/animation/armatures/posing/bone_constraints/inverse_kinematics/spline_ik.rst:57
msgid "Offset Controls"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/animation/armatures/posing/bone_constraints/inverse_kinematics/spline_ik.rst:59
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"The entire bone chain can be made to follow the shape of the curve while "
"still being able to be placed at an arbitrary point in 3D space when the "
"'Chain Offset' option is enabled. By default, this option is not enabled,"
" and the bones will be made to follow the curve in its untransformed "
"position."
msgstr ""
"L'os entier peut être fait pour suivre la forme de la courbe placé à un "
"point arbitraire dans l'espace 3D quand l'option *Chain Offset* es "
"activée. Par défaut, cette option n'est pas activée et les os seront "
"faits pour suivre la courbe dans sa position non transformée. "

#: ../../manual/animation/armatures/posing/bone_constraints/inverse_kinematics/spline_ik.rst:66
msgid "Thickness Controls"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/animation/armatures/posing/bone_constraints/inverse_kinematics/spline_ik.rst:68
msgid ""
"The thickness of the bones in the chain is controlled using the "
"constraint's 'XZ Scale Mode' setting. This setting determines the method "
"used for determining the scaling on the X and Z axes of each bone in the "
"chain."
msgstr ""
"L'épaisseur des os dans la chaîne est contrôlée en utilisant le paramètre"
" *XZ Scale Mode* de la contrainte. Ce paramètre détermine la méthode "
"utilisée pour la détermination de la mise à l'échelle sur les axes X et Z"
" de chaque os dans la chaine."

#: ../../manual/animation/armatures/posing/bone_constraints/inverse_kinematics/spline_ik.rst:72
msgid "The available modes are:"
msgstr "Les modes disponibles sont :"

#: ../../manual/animation/armatures/posing/bone_constraints/inverse_kinematics/spline_ik.rst:74
msgid "None"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/animation/armatures/posing/bone_constraints/inverse_kinematics/spline_ik.rst:75
#, fuzzy
msgid "this option keeps the X and Z scaling factors as 1.0."
msgstr "Cette option conserve les facteurs de mise à l'échelle de X et Z à 1.0. "

#: ../../manual/animation/armatures/posing/bone_constraints/inverse_kinematics/spline_ik.rst:77
msgid "Volume Preserve"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/animation/armatures/posing/bone_constraints/inverse_kinematics/spline_ik.rst:77
msgid ""
"the X and Z scaling factors are taken as the inverse of the Y scaling "
"factor (length of the bone), maintaining the 'volume' of the bone."
msgstr ""
"les facteurs de mise à l'échelle de X et Z sont prises comme l'inverse du"
" facteur de mise à l'échelle de Y (longueur de l'os), en conservant le "
"\"volume\" de l'os. "

#: ../../manual/animation/armatures/posing/bone_constraints/inverse_kinematics/spline_ik.rst:80
msgid "Bone Original"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/animation/armatures/posing/bone_constraints/inverse_kinematics/spline_ik.rst:80
msgid ""
"this options just uses the X and Z scaling factors the bone would have "
"after being evaluated in the standard way."
msgstr ""
"Cette option utilise simplement les facteurs de mise à l'échelle de X et "
"Z que l'os aurait après son évaluation de manière standard."

#: ../../manual/animation/armatures/posing/bone_constraints/inverse_kinematics/spline_ik.rst:82
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"In addition to these modes, there is an option, *Use Curve Radius*. When "
"this option is enabled, the average radius of the radii of the points on "
"the curve where the joints of each bone are placed, are used to derive X "
"and Z scaling factors. This allows the scaling effects, determined using "
"the modes above, to be tweaked as necessary for artistic control."
msgstr ""
"En plus de ces modes, il existe une option, *Use Curve Radius*. Quand "
"cette option est activée, le rayon moyen des rayons des points sur la "
"courbe où les articulations de chaque os sont placées, sont utilisées "
"pour dériver les facteurs de mise à l'échelle de X et Z. Ceci permet les "
"effets de mise à l'échelle, déterminés en utilisant les modes ci-dessus, "
"pour être fignolés autant que nécessaire pour un contrôle artistique. "

#: ../../manual/animation/armatures/posing/bone_constraints/inverse_kinematics/spline_ik.rst:90
msgid "Tips for Nice Setups"
msgstr "Astuces pour des configurations sympas."

#: ../../manual/animation/armatures/posing/bone_constraints/inverse_kinematics/spline_ik.rst:92
msgid ""
"For optimal deformations, it is recommended that the bones are roughly "
"the same length, and that they are not too long, to facilitate a better "
"fit to the curve. Also, bones should ideally be created in a way that "
"follows the shape of the curve in its 'rest pose' shape, to minimize the "
"problems in areas where the curve has sharp bends which may be especially"
" noticeable when stretching is disabled."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/animation/armatures/posing/bone_constraints/inverse_kinematics/spline_ik.rst:97
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"For control of the curve, it is recommended that hooks (in particular, "
"Bone Hooks) are used to control the control points of the curve, with one"
" hook per control point. In general, only a few control points should be "
"needed for the curve (e.g. one for every 3-5 bones offers decent "
"control)."
msgstr ""
"Pour le contrôle de la courbe, il est recommandé que les *hooks* (en "
"particulier les hooks d'os) sont utilisés pour contrôler les points de "
"contrôle de all courbe,a vec un *hook* par point de contrôle. En général,"
" seuls quelques points de contrôle devraient être nécessaires pour la "
"courbe (ex. un pour chaque groupe de 3-5 os offre un contrôle décent)."

#: ../../manual/animation/armatures/posing/bone_constraints/inverse_kinematics/spline_ik.rst:101
msgid ""
"The type of curve used does not really matter, as long as a path can be "
"extracted from it that could also be used by the Follow Path Constraint. "
"This really depends on the level of control required from the hooks."
msgstr ""
"Le type de courbe utilisé n'a pas d'importance, aussi longtemps qu'un "
"chemin peut en être extrait qui pourrait aussi être utilisé par la "
"Contrainte *Follow Path*. Ceci dépend réellement du niveau de contrôle "
"requis des *hooks*. "

#: ../../manual/animation/armatures/posing/bone_constraints/inverse_kinematics/spline_ik.rst:104
msgid ""
"When setting up the rigs, it is currently necessary to have the control "
"bones (for controlling the curve) in a separate armature to those used "
"for deforming the meshes (i.e. the deform rig containing the Spline IK "
"chains). This is to avoid creating pseudo \"Dependency Cycles\", since "
"Blender's Dependency Graph can only resolve the dependencies the control "
"bones, curves, and Spline IK'ed bones on an object by object basis."
msgstr ""

